@gjrmgjrm : It would have taken you just about the same effort to answer him as to give him a smartass comment like that.

@svgvkg : .rar files are compressed archives. You need to unpack them with a prog called WinRar into the original file. You will find it free for download just about everywhere.

Not that it makes much sense to use that on these kind of video files in the first place. They are already compressed to the max, and you would just end up with a bigger volume than you started with.
